    "Tony W. Cartledge": "421, 448",
    "John Trapp": "If thy people go out to battle. ] Upon a necessary justice, or a just necessity. For that soldier can never answer it to God that strikes not more as a justicer, than as any enemy. And shall pray unto the Lord. ] Soldiers must fight and pray, and pray and fight, as did the late king of Sweden.\nVer.\n44. If thy people go out to battle.] Upon a necessary justice, or a just necessity. For that soldier can never answer it to God that strikes not more as a justicer, than as any enemy. And shall pray unto the Lord.] Soldiers must fight and pray, and pray and fight, as did the late king of Sweden.\nVer."
