  "63": {
    "John Trapp": "And Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]` offered. ] This was the greatest sacrifice that we anywhere read of. Those hypocrites in #Mic 6:7 made an overture of great cost, so they might thereby have purchased a dispensation to live in sin. Lycurgus forbade costly sacrifices, lest men should grow weary of the charge, and give over their devotion.\nVer.\n63. And Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]` offered.] This was the greatest sacrifice that [v_Mic_6_7] we anywhere read of. Those hypocrites in #Mic 6:7 made an overture of great cost, so they might thereby have purchased a dispensation to live in sin. Lycurgus forbade costly sacrifices, lest men should grow weary of the charge, and give over their devotion.\nVer."
  },
